    • Uses of EventBatch in com.splunk.cloudfwd

      Methods in com.splunk.cloudfwd with parameters of type EventBatch 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void ConnectionCallbacks.acknowledged(EventBatch events)
      Will be called once for each EventBatch that is acknowledged (has been replicated amongst Splunk Indexers).
      void ConnectionCallbacks.checkpoint(EventBatch events)
      Checkpoint is called when there are no unacknowledged Events in-flight with an id less than or equal to events.getId().
      void ConnectionCallbacks.failed(EventBatch events, Exception ex)
      Failed will be called if their is a failure to deliver EventBatch to Splunk.
      int Connection.sendBatch(EventBatch events)
